import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Penicillin'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Penicillin')
    plt.axvline(data['Penicillin'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['Penicillin'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Penicillin')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Penicillin'], data['Streptomycin'], c=data['Gram_Staining'].astype('category').cat.codes, cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel('Penicillin')
    ax.set_ylabel('Streptomycin')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between Penicillin and Streptomycin?')
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Gram_Staining")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='Penicillin', by='Gram_Staining', ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Gram_Staining and Penicillin?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Gram_Staining')
    plt.ylabel('Penicillin')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax.legend(['positive', 'negative'], title='Gram_Staining')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
